1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as coreference resolution and pronoun disambiguation, which are part of the scope of this sub-category.
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a method that utilizes commonsense knowledge to solve a complex task, which falls under the scope of AI research.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a model for unsupervised feature extraction, which is a common task in machine learning.
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper deals with the task of resolving coreference in natural language text, which is relevant to information retrieval tasks such as document clustering and summarization.
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - Although not directly related to the paper's content, the use of embeddings and knowledge bases could potentially have implications for the computational complexity of natural language processing tasks.
